        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2398199652" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8592893727857168095">I would give this 4.5 if I could.<br/><br/>This spare, elegant classic of Catalan science fiction is taught in schools. On one level, it is a story of two young people (9 and 14) who survive an apocalyptic alien attack and start civilization over in the ruins of the old world; on another level, it is about the survival of Catalan spirit and culture despite the oppression of Franco&apos;s fascist regime. This is an excellent read for anyone interested in post-apocalypse/dystopian stories, world science fiction,</span>
  <span id="freeText8592893727857168095" style="display:none">I would give this 4.5 if I could.<br /><br />This spare, elegant classic of Catalan science fiction is taught in schools. On one level, it is a story of two young people (9 and 14) who survive an apocalyptic alien attack and start civilization over in the ruins of the old world; on another level, it is about the survival of Catalan spirit and culture despite the oppression of Franco's fascist regime. This is an excellent read for anyone interested in post-apocalypse/dystopian stories, world science fiction, science fiction in translation, or young adult science fiction.<br /><br />Edited to Add: My longer review is available <a href="http://www.starshipsofa.com/blog/2018/08/02/starship-sofa-no-549-michael-reid/" rel="nofollow noopener">in my "Looking Back on Genre History" segment on Episode 549</a> of the <i>StarShipSofa</i> podcast.</span>
